JOHANNESBURG – Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu has died from COVID-19 related complications
on Thursday. President Cyril Ramaphosa has confirmed his passing in a statement released a short while ago.  The president has extended his condolences to the minister’s family and colleagues. “Minister Mthembu was an exemplary leader, an activist and life-long champion of freedom and democracy. He was a much-loved and greatly respected colleague and comrade, whose passing leaves our nation at a loss.” – Eyewitness News 